 189   
 190  *MOL: not considering oil as feedstock, reccommendation of FUTNERC (14/02/2025)
 191  *From the current perspective, and according to FUTNERC input, at the moment very little chemical industries use directly crude oil to produce e.g., plastics), and the ones that use have some kind of internal processing.
 192  *Accordingly, at the moment, crude oil is not being directly used as feedstock, but instead petro represented refined oil that can be used directly as feedstock.
 193  *Added ammonia as feedstock - fertilizers
 194  *For future work, looking at the possibility of CH4 being also used to produce petro (paper 4 Maria OL)
