 690  max_feed(feed)  Feedstock fractions
 691  *biogas ethanol and biodiesel are at the moment not activated in the model (methanol is the proxy for all type liquid synthetic fuels)
 692  *From the current perspective, and according to FUTNERC input, at the moment very little chemical industries use directly crude oil to produce e.g., plastics), and the ones that use have some kind of internal processing.
 693  *Accordingly, at the moment, crude oil is not being directly used as feedstock, but instead petro represented refined oil that can be used directly as feedstock.
 694  *FUTNERC also suggested to dismiss coal directly as feedstock
 695  *For future work, looking at the possibility of CH4 being also used to produce petro (paper 4 Maria OL)
 696  *Coal was added back
 697  *FMK comment oil can be also considered as low cost fraction like naphtha is used in industry
